			<h2 class="date-header">Thursday, September 08, 2005</h2>
	
	<div class="entry" id="entry-6362072">
					<h3 class="entry-header">Noteworthy...</h3>
		
		<div class="entry-content">
			<div class="entry-body">
				<p>The following are a few food, wine, film and Katrina relief benefit events taking place in the Seattle area. 

</p>

<p><strong><a href="http://www.flyingfishseattle.com/events.html">Flying Fish Restaurant</a></strong>: <strong>Wine with Chris and Brian</strong>. September 14th at 6:30 ($55) and <strong>Meet the Producer Fair</strong>,<strong>&nbsp;</strong>Saturday, 17th 2005, 11:00 – 3:00 ($15 at the door)</p>

<p><strong><a href="http://www.chelanwine.com/index.php?page_id=12&amp;newsletter_id=29">3rd Annual Lake Chelan Wine Festival</a> </strong>September 10th, 4:30-7:30<strong></strong></p>





<p><strong><a href="http://www.nwfilmforum.org/">Northwest Film Forum</a></strong> <strong>Beneft for New Orleans</strong>: NWFF and New Yorker Films present
<strong>Down by Law</strong>, a film by Jim Jarmusch.
100% of proceeds to go to Red Cross. Pay what you can, $10 minimum. Sept 16-18, Fri-Sun at 7 &amp; 9:15pm. <br /><em><br />(NWFF does not serve food but they do have candy and if you drink pop, their Coke comes in vintage glass bottles. After the film, go across the street for dinner at <strong><a href="http://www.1200bistro.com/">1200 Bistro</a></strong>, my favorite pre and after NWFF movie eatery. Sit at the bar, discuss the film, nosh. They have a great wine list by the glass, the food is fabulous and the atmosphere is welcoming.</em><br /><br /><strong><a href="http://www.tomdouglas.com/relief.html">Hurricane Relief Reception</a></strong> to benefit America's Second Harvest. Thursday, September 29, 2005, 7 p.m. - 11 p.m at the Palace Ballroom (2100 5th Avenue Seattle, WA 98121) $100 per person. For reservations, please call (206) 448-2001 or email office@tomdouglas.com<br /><br /> </p>

<p>A couple noteworthy articles to read, from Wednesday's papers:<br /><br />

</p>

<p><strong><a href="http://seattlepi.nwsource.com/podcast/onfood.asp">Hsiao-Ching Chou's</a>&nbsp; </strong> <strong><a href="http://seattlepi.nwsource.com/food/239599_basketcopy07.html">This little bag went to market</a></strong>

</p>

