			<h2 class="date-header">Thursday, March 31, 2005</h2>
	
	<div class="entry" id="entry-4141027">
					<h3 class="entry-header">EoMEoTE #5: Hard boiled eggs, toast sticks & Salumi Hot Sopressata</h3>
		
		<div class="entry-content">
			<div class="entry-body">
				<p><a href="http://seattlebonvivant.typepad.com/.shared/image.html?/photos/uncategorized/1_10.JPG" onclick="window.open(this.href, '_blank', 'width=448,height=336,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0'); return false"><img width="275" height="206" border="0" alt="1_10" title="1_10" src="http://seattlebonvivant.typepad.com/seattle_bon_vivant/images/1_10.JPG" /></a></p>





<p>A little morning breakfast and my entry to the latest <strong><a href="http://thepassionatecook.typepad.com/thepassionatecook/2005/03/announcing_the_.html">EoMEoTE</a></strong>--which I still giggle about every time I see the hilarious acronym--created by fellow bloggers <strong><a href="http://spiceblog.blogspot.com/">Anthony</a></strong> and <strong><a href="http://cooksister.typepad.com/">Jeanne</a></strong> and hosted by<strong> Jo</strong> of <strong><a href="http://thepassionatecook.typepad.com/thepassionatecook/">The Passionate Cook</a></strong>. </p>

<p>A couple free range, organic eggs that were simply hard boiled and sprinkled with freshly ground black pepper and <strong>Casina Rossa <em>Truffle &amp; Salt</em></strong>. A side of Buttermilk toast sliced into sticks and some delicious <em>Hot Sopressata</em> from my favorite cured meats purveyor, <strong>Armandino Batali</strong> of <strong><a href="http://www.salumicuredmeats.com/">Salumi Cured Meats</a></strong>, here in downtown Seattle. </p>

<p>A cup of strong Illy coffee with cream and sugar and I'm ready to face the day.<br />
</p>
			</div>
			
			
			
		</div>
		<p class="entry-footer">
			<span class="post-footers">09:40 AM</span> <span class="separator">|</span> <a class="permalink" href="http://seattlebonvivant.typepad.com/seattle_bon_vivant/2005/03/eomeote_5_hard_.html">Permalink</a>
