	<div class="entry" id="entry-1689781">
					<h3 class="entry-header">Seattle Wine Society's 30th Anniversary NW Wine and Food Festival</h3>
		
		<div class="entry-content">
			<div class="entry-body">
				<p>"Come celebrate three decades of excellence at Seattle Wine Society 30th Anniversary <strong><A href="http://www.enosoc.org/FairAndFestival/2004%20Festival/NW_Wine_Festival%20_2004.htm">NW Wine and Food Festival</A></strong> .  The longest running local wine competition, this annual event features <strong>up to 200 wines, dinner, and dance band entertainment</strong>. Every entered Washington, Oregon, Idaho and British Columbia wine will be available for tasting.</p>

<p>Ticket prices have remained unchanged for three years. And unlike other events where food is minimal or must be purchased separately, admission <strong>includes all wine tasting and a four-course meal</strong>. Also free specialty food samples, souvenir program, commemorative wineglass, award list and on-site parking.</p>

<p>An optional <strong>Flavors and Flaws</strong> wine education seminar at 2:30 preceding the Festival will be an interactive and entertaining approach to learning the basics and beyond of recognizing the most important components in wine. This is an opportunity for you to become more aware of how these elements interact to flavor wine. What a great way to prepare for the Festival! Cost is $30 ($25 Wine Society members). Reservations required for both events." </p>

<p>Click here for a  <strong><A href="http://www.enosoc.org/FairAndFestival/2004%20Festival/Brochure_Festival04.pdf">Festival brochure with reservation forml</A></strong></p>

<p><strong>30th Anniversary Northwest Wine & Food Festival<br />
Saturday, August 7, 2004<br />
5 to 9:30 p.m.<br />
South Seattle Community College Plaza<br />
$60 Wine Society Members<br />
$70 Non-members<br />
Festival limited to 600 attendees. <br />
Contact Gail Meldrum, 425-775-7168</strong></p>
