			<h2 class="date-header">Monday, June 21, 2004</h2>
	
	<div class="entry" id="entry-1632876">
					<h3 class="entry-header">Warm roasted beet, fig and red young onion salad</h3>
		
		<div class="entry-content">
			<div class="entry-body">
				<p><a href="http://seattlebonvivant.typepad.com/seattle_bon_vivant/images/IMG_19181.html" onclick="window.open('http://seattlebonvivant.typepad.com/seattle_bon_vivant/images/IMG_19181.html','popup','width=328,height=448,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0'); return false"><img alt="IMG_1918" src="http://seattlebonvivant.typepad.com/seattle_bon_vivant/images/IMG_1918-thumb.JPG" width="175" height="275" border="0" style="float: right; margin: 0px 0px 5px 5px;" /></a></p>

<p><a href="http://seattlebonvivant.typepad.com/seattle_bon_vivant/images/alvarez_farms_beets1.html" onclick="window.open('http://seattlebonvivant.typepad.com/seattle_bon_vivant/images/alvarez_farms_beets1.html','popup','width=448,height=336,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0'); return false"><img alt="alvarez_farms_beets" src="http://seattlebonvivant.typepad.com/seattle_bon_vivant/images/alvarez_farms_beets-thumb.JPG" width="100" height="75" border="0" style="float: left; margin: 0px 5px 5px 0px;" /></a>Beets, garnet red and highly nutritious are in season year round. But yesterday, while at Pike Place Market we purchased beautifully fat ones from the friendly guys at the <strong>Alvarez Farms</strong> stand (out on the sidewalk, a few stands away from our mushroom guy) .<BR><BR><a href="http://seattlebonvivant.typepad.com/seattle_bon_vivant/images/warm_beetfig_and_red_onion_salad1.html" onclick="window.open('http://seattlebonvivant.typepad.com/seattle_bon_vivant/images/warm_beetfig_and_red_onion_salad1.html','popup','width=336,height=337,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0'); return false"><img alt="warm_beetfig_and_red_onion_salad" src="http://seattlebonvivant.typepad.com/seattle_bon_vivant/images/warm_beetfig_and_red_onion_salad-thumb.JPG" width="100" height="100" border="0" style="float: left; margin: 0px 5px 5px 0px;" /></a><br />
So, last night for <strong><A href="http://seattlebonvivant.typepad.com/seattle_bon_vivant/2004/06/tarragon_honey_.html">IMBB No. 5: Catch of the Day-Fish</A></strong> I served a <strong>Warm roasted beet, fig and red young onion salad</strong> .  Its a very simple salad really. The figs, onions and beets work so well together. The Balsamic Vinegar intensifies the flavors.  Sweet. The figs and onions caramelized. Just lovely.</p>

<p><strong>Warm roasted beet, fig and red young onion salad</strong></p>

<p><strong>In a bowl combine:<br />
About 6 Black Mission figs (quartered)<br />
One bunch early red onions (quartered)<br />
Four medium sized beets (washed gently, stems trimmed to about one inch) </strong></p>

<p><strong>Toss the begetables with the best <strong>Extra Virgin Olive Oil</strong> and <strong>Balsamic Vinegar you have around. Salt and pepper to taste. Place in oven proof dish at 350F for about an hour or until beets are tender when pierced with skewer. Serve warm.</strong></p>

<p></p>

<p></p>

<p><br />
<strong>Alvarez Farms<br />
Fresh Organic Produce<br />
(Over 100 different types of vegetables)<br />
340 Murray Road<br />
Mabton, WA 98935<br />
(509) 837 2381</strong></p>
			</div>
			
			
			
		</div>
