			<h2 class="date-header">Monday, June 07, 2004</h2>
	
	<div class="entry" id="entry-1544788">
					<h3 class="entry-header">Sunday brunch at Café Campagne</h3>
		
		<div class="entry-content">
			<div class="entry-body">
				<p><img alt="dahlia_bakerys_peppermint_patty_cookie" src="http://seattlebonvivant.typepad.com/seattle_bon_vivant/images/dahlia_bakerys_peppermint_patty_cookie.JPG" width="270" height="203" border="0"  /><BR><BR>Early yesterday morning we got up to have a little breakfast with our friend F at <strong><A href="http://seattlebonvivant.typepad.com/seattle_bon_vivant/2004/05/dahlias_ficelle.html">Dahlia Bakery</A></strong>. This was the first Sunday of their new Summer Sunday schedule. Opening every Sunday 10-4, serving all their wonderful usual fare: coffee, sandwiches, salads, freshly baked breads, tarts, pies, cookies, cakes and the like.<BR><BR>After what seemed like an hour of people watching, great conversation, coffee, sandwiches, brioche, Grandma Douglas’ Schnecken and feeding the little birds that come to greet you at the sidewalk tables we took off for a visit to the <strong>Seattle Library</strong> . What a fabulous building! After, a leasurely walk up First Avenue towards Pike Place Market (I'll be posting the photos of the day later this afternoon) , a stop at the Alexis Hotel and <strong>brunch</strong> at <strong>Café Campagne</strong>.<BR><BR><img alt="caf_campagne_brunch_menu" src="http://seattlebonvivant.typepad.com/seattle_bon_vivant/images/caf_campagne_brunch_menu.JPG" width="270" height="203" border="0"  /><BR><BR>By the time we walked up to Café Campagne we were starving, thirsty and ready for a break. The hostess found us a great table by one of their patio doors that helps us cool off while we ordered our beverages. Fresh pinneapple and orange juices, coffee. A Demi-baguette served with local honey, wonderful butter and fresh apricot jam was the perfect start for our little late-afternoon brunch.<BR><BR><img alt="caf_campagne_oeufs_en_meurette" src="http://seattlebonvivant.typepad.com/seattle_bon_vivant/images/caf_campagne_oeufs_en_meurette.JPG" width="270" height="203" border="0"  /><BR><BR>We all ordered the same meal. <strong>Oeufs en Meurette</strong> . These are two poached eggs served on garlic croutons, bacon and champignons, in a red wine and fois gras sauce served with pommes frittes. </p>

<p>This is one of my favorite dishes at Café Campagne so I do not mind ordering it over and over. As every other time, it was delicious.<BR><BR><img alt="caf_campagne_terrace" src="http://seattlebonvivant.typepad.com/seattle_bon_vivant/images/caf_campagne_terrace.JPG" width="270" height="203" border="0"  /><BR><BR></p>

<p><br />
By the by...<strong>La Terrasse</strong> at Campagne is now open for the summer. Dining en <em>plein air</em> has never been lovelier</p>

<p><strong><A href="http://www.cafecampagne.com/home/home.cfml">Café Campagne</A></strong><br />
1600 Post Alley at Pine<br />
Seattle, WA 98101<br />
206.728.2233</strong></p>

